{"title_page": "Micha\u00ebl Jeremiasz", "text_new": "{{short description|French wheelchair tennis player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox wheelchair tennis player\n| name                              = Micha\u00ebl J\u00e9r\u00e9miasz\n| image                             = \n| caption                           = <!-- brief text caption for the image -->\n| full_name                         = \n| nickname                          = \n| country                           = {{Flagu|France}}\n| residence                         = \n| birth_date                        = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1981|10|15}}\n| birth_place                       = [[Paris]], France\n| death_date                        = \n| death_place                       = \n| turnedpro                         = \n| retired                           = \n| plays                             = Right handed\n| careerprizemoney                  = \n| tennishofyear                     = <!-- year inducted into the Tennis Hall of Fame -->\n| tennishofid                       = <!-- ID from the Tennis HoF website, taken from http://www.tennisfame.com/hall-of-famers/First Name-Last Name i.e. martina-navratilova, which it is all undercase letters-->\n| website                           = \n| singlesrecord                     = \n| singlestitles                     = \n| highestsinglesranking             = '''No.1''' (2005)\n| currentsinglesranking             = \n| AustralianOpenresult              = \n| FrenchOpenresult                  = \n| USOpenresult                      = \n| Othertournaments                  = yes\n| WheelchairTennisMastersresult     = F (2004, 2005, 2007)\n| Paralympicsresult                 = [[File:Bronze medal Paralympics.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] '''Bronze Medal''' (2004)\n| doublesrecord                     = \n| doublestitles                     = \n| highestdoublesranking             = '''No.1''' (2004)\n| currentdoublesranking             = \n| grandslamsdoublesresults          = \n| AustralianOpenDoublesresult       = '''W''' (2013)\n| FrenchOpenDoublesresult           = '''W''' (2009)\n| WimbledonDoublesresult            = '''W''' (2009, 2012)\n| USOpenDoublesresult               = '''W''' (2005, 2006)\n| OthertournamentsDoubles           = Yes\n| WheelchairTennisMastersDoublesresult   = '''W''' (2005, 2007)\n| ParalympicsDoublesresult          = [[File:Gold medal Paralympics.svg|20px]] '''Gold Medal''' (2008)<br />[[File:Bronze medal Paralympics.svg|20px]] '''Bronze Medal''' (2012)\n| WheelchairWorldTeamCupresult      = \n| updated                           = <!-- adds date this template was last updated at an individual article -->\n| medaltemplates                    =\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[wheelchair tennis]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{Flagu|France}} }}\n{{MedalGold | [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]] | [[Wheelchair tennis at the 2008 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Men's doubles|Men's doubles]] }}\n{{MedalSilver | [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Athens]] | [[Wheelchair Tennis at the 2004 Summer Paralympics|Men's doubles]] }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Athens]] | [[Wheelchair Tennis at the 2004 Summer Paralympics|Men's singles]] }}\n}}\n\n'''Micha\u00ebl J\u00e9r\u00e9miasz''' (born 15 October 1981 in [[Paris]]) is a former professional [[wheelchair tennis]] player from France. He won a gold medal in the men's doubles event at the [[2008 Summer Paralympics|Paralympic Games]] in Beijing 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wheelchair Tennis Review: Wheelchair Tennis ends with Japan, Netherlands and France winners |date=15 September 2008 |publisher=The Beijing Organizing Committee for the Games of the XXIX Olympiad |url=http://en.paralympic.beijing2008.cn/news/sports/wheelchairtennis/n214604041.shtml |accessdate=25 September 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090916140234/http://en.paralympic.beijing2008.cn/news/sports/wheelchairtennis/n214604041.shtml |archivedate=16 September 2009 }}</ref> Jeremiasz has been World Number 1 for doubles and singles on the wheelchair circuit. Jeremiasz, as of 19 May 2007, is 4th for singles and 1st for doubles. Jeremiasz is right-handed and likes hard courts. He is coached by Jerome Delbert.\n\n==Grand Slam titles==\n\n===Doubles===\n* [[2003 Australian Open]] (w/[[David Hall (tennis)|Hall]])\n* [[2005 US Open (tennis)|2005 US Open]] (w/[[Robin Ammerlaan|Ammerlaan]])\n* [[2006 US Open (tennis)|2006 US Open]] (w/Ammerlaan)\n* [[2009 French Open]] (w/[[St\u00e9phane Houdet|Houdet]])\n* [[2009 Wimbledon Championships]] (w/[[St\u00e9phane Houdet|Houdet]])\n* [[2012 Wimbledon Championships]] (w/[[Tom Egberink|Egberink]])\n\n==Singles performance timeline==\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center;font-size:97%\n! Tournament !! 2003 !! 2005 !! 2006 !! 2007 !! 2008 !! 2009 !! 2011 !! SR !! W\u2013L\n|-\n| colspan=18 align=left | '''Grand Slams'''\n|-\n| align=left | Australian Open\n| bgcolor=ffebcd | [[2003 Australian Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|QF]]\n|\n| bgcolor=lime | [[2006 Australian Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|'''W''']]\n| bgcolor=thistle | [[2007 Australian Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|F]]\n| bgcolor=thistle | [[2008 Australian Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|F]]\n| bgcolor=yellow | [[2009 Australian Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|SF]]\n|\n| 1 / 5\n| 8\u20134\n|-\n| align=left | French Open\n|\n|\n|\n| bgcolor=yellow | [[2007 French Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|SF]]\n|\n| bgcolor=yellow | [[2009 French Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|SF]]\n| bgcolor=ffebcd | [[2011 French Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|QF]]\n| 0 / 3\n| 2\u20133\n|-\n| align=left | [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 0 / 0\n| 0\u20130\n|-\n| align=left | [[US Open (tennis)|US Open]]\n|\n| bgcolor=thistle | [[2005 US Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|F]]\n| bgcolor=thistle | [[2006 US Open \u2013 Wheelchair Men's Singles|F]]\n| bgcolor=ffebcd | [[2007 US Ope