 2008 |journal = [[ChartsPlus]] |issue = 369 |pages= 9 |publisher = IQ Ware Ltd |location = Milton Keynes}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US ''Billboard'' Top Soundtracks\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|}\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2008)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US ''Billboard'' 200<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2008/top-billboard-200-albums|title=Billboard 200 Albums \u2013 Year-End 2008|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref>\n| 26\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2009)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US ''Billboard'' 200<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2009/top-billboard-200-albums|title=Billboard 200 Albums \u2013 Year-End 2009|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref>\n| 188\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Brazil|title=Camp Rock|artist=Diversos|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=2008|certyear=2009}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=France|title=Camp Rock |artist=BOF|type=album|award=Gold|relyear=2008|certyear=2009|certmonth=12}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Mexico|title=Camp Rock |artist=Varios|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=2008}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|title=Camp Rock OST|artist=Camp Rock Cast|type=album|award=Gold|recent=true}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Spain|title=Camp Rock |artist=B.S.O.|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=2008|certyear=2008|certmonth=52}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Camp Rock |artist=Various Artists|type=album|award=Silver}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Camp Rock |artist=Soundtrack|type=album|award=Platinum}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=GCC|title=Camp Rock |artist=OST|type=album|award=Gold|certyear=2009}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist-ua|30em}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.disneychannel.com/camprock Official Camp Rock Site]\n\n{{Camp Rock}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Camp Rock (soundtrack)}}\n[[Category:Albums produced by Greg Wells]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Matthew Gerrard]]\n[[Category:Disney film soundtracks]]\n[[Category:2008 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Television soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Records soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Camp Rock|Soundtrack 1]]\n[[Category:Cast recordings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Camp Rock\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = ''[[Camp Rock]]'' Cast\n| image      = Camp Rock Soundtrack.JPG\n| alt        =\n| released   = June 17, 2008\n| recorded   = 2007\n| genre      = {{flat list|\n*[[Pop rock]]\n*[[teen pop]]}}\n| length     = 39:26\n| label      = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| producer   = {{flat list|\n* [[Adam Watts (musician)|Adam Watts]]\n* [[Andy Dodd]]\n* [[Kara DioGuardi]]\n* [[Mitch Allan]]\n* [[Greg Wells]]\n}}\n| chronology = ''Camp Rock'' soundtracks\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (soundtrack)|Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n| misc       = {{Singles\n| Name           = Camp Rock\n| Type           = soundtrack\n| single 1       = [[We Rock (Camp Rock song)|We Rock]]\n| Single 1 date  = April 19, 2008 \n| Single 2       = [[Play My Music]]\n| Single 2 date  = May 3, 2008\n| Single 3       = Start the Party\n| Single 3 date  = May 23, 2008\n| Single 4       = [[This Is Me (Demi Lovato song)|This Is Me]]\n| Single 4 date  = June 17, 2008\n| Single 5       = Too Cool\n| Single 5 date  = June 24, 2008\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Camp Rock''''' is the [[soundtrack album]] from the 2008 [[Disney Channel]] [[Camp Rock|television film of the same name]]. The album was released on June 17, 2008 by [[Walt Disney Records]]. Full songs of the album were made available on ''Camp Rock''{{'}}s official web site for one week beginning June 10, 2008, and the full soundtrack premiered on Radio Disney on June 14, 2008, during ''Planet Premiere: Camp Rock''. The soundtrack was released in the UK on July 14, 2008.\n\n==Background==\nThe soundtrack album (both original and two-disc collector's edition) is an enhanced CD which contains a clip of an acoustic version of \"This Is Me\" when played on the computer with internet access. On November 16, 2008, a karaoke/instrumental version of the ''Camp Rock'' soundtrack was released. It is not available on iTunes, but it can be purchased in stores such as [[Walmart]], [[Target Corporation|Target]], etc.\n\n==Chart performance==\nThe soundtrack reached number two on the US [[iTunes Store]] on the first two days of its release<ref>[https://archive.today/20120718112625/http://phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?id=282159547&s=143441 US iTunes Music Store]</ref> and number four on the Canadian iTunes Store. It debuted at number three on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 188,000 copies sold in its first week.<ref name=\"camprockbillbd3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1044979/coldplay-cruises-to-no-1-on-the-billboard-200|title=Coldplay Cruises To No. 1 On The Billboard 200|date=2008-06-25|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=2009-06-09}}</ref> It was certified Gold and Platinum in the U.S. on September 9, 2008.{{Certification Cite Ref|region=United States|title=Camp Rock |artist=Soundtrack|type=album}}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = 39:26 \n| extra_column    = Performer(s)\n| title1          = [[We Rock (Camp Rock song)|We Rock]]\n| extra1          = ''Camp Rock'' cast\n| length1         = 3:14\n\n| title2          = [[Play My Music]]\n| extra2          = [[Jonas Brothers]]\n| length2         = 3:21\n| title3          = Gotta Find You\n| extra3          = [[Joe Jonas]]\n| length3         = 4:03\n| title5          = Start th