tegory:Treaties extended to Montserrat]]\n[[Category:Treaties extended to the Pitcairn Islands]]\n[[Category:Treaties extended to Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]]\n[[Category:Treaties extended to South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands]]\n[[Category:Treaties extended to the Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n[[Category:Treaties extended to British Hong Kong]]\n", "name_user": "DavidMCEddy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eViolations of the NPT:delete unnecessary comma", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_on_the_Non-Proliferation_of_Nuclear_Weapons"}
{"title_page": "Vinayakan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Vinayakan\n| image              = File:Vinayakan 5z .jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Vinayakan T. K.\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = Thoppil Jn, [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = [[Film , singer\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| awards             = [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor]] (2016)\n| website            = \n| known for          = \n| years active       = 1995\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Vinayakan''' is an Indian [[film]]\n[[actor]] who predominantly works in the [[Malayalam Film Industry]].<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Malayalam Movies acted by Vinayakan|url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/movieslist.php?a=7446|publisher=Malayala Chalachithram|accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref> Apart, he also works in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]], [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Bollywood]] films.<ref name=MusicDirector>{{cite web|last1=Anand|first1=Shilp Nair|title=On the superhero trail|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/on-the-superhero-trail/article4785988.ece|publisher=The Hindu|accessdate=20 September 2016|date=6 June 2013}}</ref><ref name=MusicVinayakan>{{cite web|last1=\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d7c|first1=\u0d05\u0d28\u0d40\u0d37\u0d4d|title=\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d05\u0d38\u0d42\u0d2f\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d05\u0d39\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/interview/vinayakan-kammattipaadammovie-malayalamfilm-malayalam-news-1.1079869|publisher=Mathrubhumi|accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref> He started his career with a cameo appearance in [[Thampi Kannanthanam]]'s 1997 film ''[[Maanthrikam]]''.Later, he did a couple of films as supporting roles as well as comedian roles respectively.In 2016, Vinayakan won the [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor]] for his performance of ''Ganga'' in [[Rajiv Ravi]]'s ''[[Kammatipaadam]]'' and also well appreciated by the critics.<ref>[http://zeenews.india.com/regional/kerala-state-films-awards-2016-vinayakan-bags-best-actor-trophy-rajisha-vijayan-adjudged-best-actress_1984312.html \"Kerala State Awards 2016: full list of winners...\"]. ''Zee News''. 7 March 2016. Retrieved 7 March 2016.</ref> He also composed a song for the film.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/i-never-felt-i-was-inferior-and-that-empowered-me-vinayakan/articleshow/57576215.cms|title=I never felt I was inferior and that empowered me: Vinayakan |work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n===Acting===\nVinayakan began his career as a dancer and had a dance troupe named ''Black Mercury'' with [[Fire dance]] being his forte. Director [[Thampi Kannanthanam]] introduced him in ''[[Maanthrikam]]'' and later in ''[[Onnaman]]''. He was noticed for his performances in  ''[[Stop Violence]]'' and [[Mohanlal]] starrer [[Chotta Mumbai]].<ref name=MusicDirector/><ref name=MusicVinayakan/>\n\nVinayakan was unanimously appreciated for the performance as Ganga in [[Rajeev Ravi]]' s 2016 film ''[[Kammatipaadam]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last1=VS|first1=Goutham|title=Dulquer Salmaan shines in a raw and realistic cut into the brutally buried history of Dalits|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/kammatipaadam-movie-review-dulquer-salmaan-shines-in-a-raw-and-realistic-cut-into-the-brutally-buried-history-of-dalits-2811732/|newspaper=The Indian Express|accessdate=20 September 2016|date=21 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kammatti Paadam Movie Review|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/kammatti-paadam-malayalam-movie-review-20718.html|publisher=India Glitz|accessdate=20 September 2016|date=21 May 2016}}</ref> and nominated for national award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/vinayakan-was-not-in-the-final-four-for-best-actor/articleshow/58066847.cms|title=Vinayakan was not in the final four for Best Actor |work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref> where he made his debut as music director as well. His performance in the film, brought him the Best Actor Award of Kerala State Film Awards,    The North American Film Award for Outstanding performance in a film, Best Actor Award (2016) of Cinema Paradiso Club Cine Awards etc.<ref>[http://www.filmibeat.com/malayalam/news/2017/nivin-pauly-and-manju-warrier-bag-top-honours-at-nafa-2017-252998.html NAFA 2017 for Outstanding performance]</ref>\n\n===Composing and other===\nVinayakan composed the song \"Puzhu Pulikal\" for the movie ''Kammatipaadam.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/100317/vinayakan-to-do-composing-choreography.html|title=Vinayakan to do composing, choreography|date=2017-03-10|work=|access-date=2018-02-21|language=en}}</ref>''.He has also sung songs for Raffi\u2019s new film Role Models and one song for Ordinary fame Sugeeth\u2019s upcoming movie. Earlier, Vinayakan used to perform in dance troupe before coming to cinema.\n\n==Awards==\n* 2018: Best Character Actor - [[CPC Cine Awards]] (for ''[[Ee.Ma.Yau]]'')\n* 2017: Best Actor - [[CPC Cine Awards]] (for ''Kammattipaadam'')\n* 2016: [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] - [[Kerala State Film Award]] (for ''[[Kammatipaadam|Kammattipaadam]]'')\n* 2016: Best Actor - Movie Munshi Cine Awards 2016 (for ''Kammattipaadam'')\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Title \n! Year\n!Role \n!Language\n!Notes\n|-\n|Karinthandan ||TBA||Karinthandan||[[Malayalam]]||Filming\n|-\n|[[Dhruva Natchathiram]] ||2020|| ||[[Tamil language|Tamil]]|| \n|-\n|[[Trance_(2019_film)|''Trance'']]||2020||Thomas||[[Malayalam]]\n|Also done title track\n|-\n|''[[Valiyaperunnal]]''\n|2019\n|\n|[[Malayalam]]\n|\n|-\n|[